    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>An analytical technique which measures quantifiable aspects of a stone’s porosity by forcing a non-wetting liquid, such as mercury, into the pores of the material using a porosimeter. The technique is used in archaeological conservation to determine the durability and behavior of ancient stone and the choice of conservation methods</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
